name: Sandwich
description: An item of food consisting of two pieces of bread with a filling between them, eaten as a light meal.

name: Pasta
description: Food made from flour, water, and sometimes egg, that is cooked and usually served with a sauce. It is made in various shapes that have different names.

name: French Fries
description: Long, thin pieces of potato that are fried and eaten hot.

name: Burger
description: A flat round cake of minced potatoes mixed with other vegetables, fried or grilled and typically served in a bread roll garnished with various condiments.

name: Pizza
description: A dish of Italian origin, consisting of a flat round base of dough baked with a topping of tomatoes and cheese, typically with added meat, fish, or vegetables.

name: Coke
description: A carbonated non-alcoholic drink manufactured by the Coca-Cola Company.

name: Sprite
description: Sprite is a colorless, caffeine-free, lemon and lime-flavored soft drink created by The Coca-Cola Company.

name: Mountain-Dew
description: Mountain Dew is a carbonated soft drink brand produced and owned by PepsiCo

name: Tea
description: A hot drink made by infusing the dried crushed leaves of the tea plant in boiling water.

name: Coffee
description: A hot drink made from the roasted and ground seeds (coffee beans) of a tropical shrub.

name: Chips
description: A long rectangular piece of deep-fried potato.

name: Nachos
description: A dish of tortilla chips topped with melted cheese and often also with other savoury toppings.

name: Namkeen
description: A small savoury snack or dish.

name: Lays
description: Potato chips varieties produced by Frito-Lay.

name: Pringles
description: Brand of potato and wheat-based stackable snack chips.

name: Rolled Biscuits
description: Rolled biscuits are one of the most popular baking-powder leavened quick breads.

name: Drop Biscuits
description: Drop biscuits have more milk or other liquid added to the dough than rolled biscuits. The dough is moister and cannot be kneaded or rolled.

name: Scones
description: Scones are sweet, rich wedge-shaped biscuits that are usually made with cream as well as butter. Scones have a tender, heavy crumb and a slightly crusty brown top.

name: Shortcakes
description: Shortcakes use rich biscuits or scones as a base. They are either split or served whole, topped with sweetened fruit and whipped cream or ice cream.

name: Viennese whirls
description: Viennese whirls are a sandwich biscuit made up of two shortbread biscuits held together with raspberry jam and buttercream.

name: Cookies
description: A baked or cooked food that is small, flat and sweet. It usually contains flour, sugar and some type of oil or fat. It may include other ingredients such as raisins, oats, chocolate chips, nuts, etc.

name: Cake
description: An item of soft sweet food made from a mixture of flour, fat, eggs, sugar, and other ingredients, baked and sometimes iced or decorated.

name: Pastry
description: A food made from a mixture of flour, fat, and water, rolledflat and either wrapped around or put over or under other foods, and then baked.

name: Pudding
description: A cooked sweet dish served after the main course of a meal.

name: Chocolate Brownies
description: A chocolate brownie is a square, baked, chocolate dessert. Brownies come in a variety of forms and may be either fudgy or cakey, depending on their density. They may include nuts, frosting, cream cheese, chocolate chips, or other ingredients
